1:1 COMMENT "# io_buffered.z -- write bytes to a file through a bufwriter, then"
1:67 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# read them back through a bufreader."
2:38 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# Phase 1b buffered wrappers in action:"
4:40 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "#   * `io.bufwriter.create to: ...lock capacity: ...` holds a borrow"
5:69 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#     on the underlying file for the wrapper's lifetime (path-scoped"
6:69 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#     lock). The source handle is inaccessible while bw is alive."
7:66 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "#   * Writes accumulate in the wrapper's buf until the capacity would"
8:70 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "#     overflow (or an explicit `flush` drains it)."
9:51 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#   * bufreader is a pass-through in Phase 1b \u{2014} internal buffering"
10:67 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "#     is added alongside textreader in Phase 1c."
11:49 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "#"
12:2 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# RAII still applies to the underlying file: the wrapper borrows"
13:65 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "# rather than owns, so scope exit on the file closes the fd."
14:61 EOL "\n"
15:1 EOL "\n"
